One of the fleeing suspects from the Kuje Correctional Centre in the Federal Capital Territory (FCT) Abuja has been recaptured in Suleja, a commercial hub in Niger State, which shares a slim boundary with Abuja. According to a press statement signed by DSP Wasiu A. Abiodun, Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO), Niger State Command disclosed the suspect, 54 years Kazeem Murtala was re-arrested on 9/07/2022 at about 2030 hours. The statement read, “Police operatives attached to ‘A’ Div Suleja while on patrol around General hospital Suleja down to Bakassi area of the commercial hub and based on credible intelligence, the operatives stormed an identified compound and arrested one Kazeem Murtala aged 54 years”. During interrogation, the inmate confessed that he escaped from Kuje Custodial Center during the attack where he was serving a jail term after conviction for an offence he committed and he has been in the custody for the past two years. Meanwhile, Niger state Commissioner of Police, Mr Monday Bala Kuryas, who commended the Suleja patrol team for the feat also directed that the inmate should be immediately transferred to the custodial centre. While also appreciating members of the general public for giving useful information and intelligence that enabled the Police to recapture the fleeing suspect called for the sustenance of such collaborative effort in the fight against crime and other forms of criminalities.